# Hierarchical Categories and Prominent Tagging

This plan outlines the implementation of a chained category filtering system and a quick-insight tagging system to help users grasp the core of a news article instantly.

## Goal Description
The objective is to implement:
1. **Chained Category Filters:** Articles will be assigned a hierarchical path of categories (e.g., `Cisco -> Networking -> Network Scanning Vulnerabilities`), and users will be able to filter articles by drilling down through this chain.
2. **Priority Tags:** Articles will have prominent metadata tags (e.g., `[Company Name]`, `[Financial Loss]`, `[Attack Type]`) displayed directly on the article card. This ensures users can get a "70% idea" of the news at a glance.

